stateDiagram-v2
    Start --> ReadErrors: Open phase-errors.toon

    ReadErrors --> CheckDataEmpty: Validate toonErrors\nlength > 0?

    CheckDataEmpty --> BuildErrorAnalysis: Yes - Iterate entries
    CheckDataEmpty --> HandleEmptyData: No - Empty data\npath

    BuildErrorAnalysis --> SortFailures: Aggregate checks\nto failures map

    SortFailures --> CountSort: Sort failures\nby count DESC\n+ L1 to end

    CountSort --> DetectOutliers: Extract timings\nfrom task context

    DetectOutliers --> CheckMinDataPoints: Validate\ndata points >= 4?

    CheckMinDataPoints --> CalculateIQR: Yes - Sort timings\nby seconds

    CheckMinDataPoints --> SkipOutliers: No - Skip\noutlier detection

    CalculateIQR --> FindOutliers: Calculate Q1, Q3,\nIQR, upperFence

    FindOutliers --> FilterOutliers: Filter seconds >\nupper fence

    FilterOutliers --> CheckOutliersFound: Outliers\ndetected?

    CheckOutliersFound --> ClassifyErrors: Yes - Add to\nBottleneckResult
    CheckOutliersFound --> ClassifyErrors: No - Continue\nwithout outliers

    SkipOutliers --> ClassifyErrors: (empty outlierPhases)

    ClassifyErrors --> GroupChecksByPhase: Build checkPhases\nMap per failure

    GroupChecksByPhase --> FindRecurring: Filter checks\nwith phases >= 3

    FindRecurring --> FindCascading: Extract phase\nnumbers & sort

    FindCascading --> DetectChains: Find consecutive\nphase sequences

    DetectChains --> FindOneOff: Check chain\nlength >= 2?

    FindOneOff --> ClassifyResult: Categorize\nremaining as\none-off

    ClassifyResult --> GenerateAdvice: Build advice array

    GenerateAdvice --> ApplyAdviceRules: Check ADVICE_RULES\nfor pattern matches

    ApplyAdviceRules --> ApplyThreshold: Check failures\ncount >= 5?

    ApplyThreshold --> CheckTddRedFlag: Yes - Add threshold\nadvice

    ApplyThreshold --> SkipThreshold: No - Skip\nthreshold check

    CheckTddRedFlag --> GenerateOutlierAdvice: Check\noutlierPhases\nlength > 0?

    SkipThreshold --> GenerateOutlierAdvice: (proceed)

    GenerateOutlierAdvice --> AddOutlierAdvice: Yes - Add session\ninterruption warning\nfor each outlier

    GenerateOutlierAdvice --> SkipOutlierAdvice: No - Skip\noutlier advice

    AddOutlierAdvice --> BuildAnalytics: (advice complete)

    SkipOutlierAdvice --> BuildAnalytics: (advice complete)

    HandleEmptyData --> BuildAnalytics: (empty collections)

    BuildAnalytics --> IntegrateResults: Merge:\nerrorAnalysis +\nerrorHistory +\nbottlenecks +\nadvice +\nerrorClassification

    IntegrateResults --> WriteToon: Call writeAnalyticsToon()\nwith full AnalyticsResult

    WriteToon --> WriteTopFailure: Parallel writes:\ntopFailure[] +\nerrorHistory[]

    WriteToon --> WriteOutliers: Parallel writes:\noutlierPhases[]?\n(optional)

    WriteToon --> WriteClassification: Parallel writes:\nerrorClassification?\n(optional)

    WriteTopFailure --> FlushToon: Merge sections\ninto analytics-toon\noutput

    WriteOutliers --> FlushToon: (continue)

    WriteClassification --> FlushToon: (continue)

    FlushToon --> ValidateToon: Validate TOON\nstructure

    ValidateToon --> CheckValidation: Valid?

    CheckValidation --> End: Yes - Write\nanalytics-toon\ncomplete

    CheckValidation --> Error: No - Schema\nviolation

    Error --> [*]: Failed

    End --> [*]: Success


%% DECISIONS
%% --------
%% D1: Empty data handling path (CheckDataEmpty state)
%%     Rationale: phase-errors.toon may be missing/empty in early sessions
%%     Fallback: Return empty errorAnalysis + empty advice + no outliers
%%     Ensures robust handling without crashing
%%
%% D2: IQR calculation guard (CheckMinDataPoints state)
%%     Threshold: 4 data points minimum (statistical necessity for Q1/Q3)
%%     Rationale: Fewer than 4 points cannot reliably compute quartiles
%%     Fallback: SkipOutliers path returns empty OutlierResult[]
%%
%% D3: Outlier decision branching (CheckOutliersFound state)
%%     Route A: outliers detected -> add to BottleneckResult.outlierPhases
%%     Route B: no outliers -> continue with empty/undefined outlierPhases
%%     Allows downstream systems to check existence vs. assume presence
%%
%% D4: Cascading detection for consecutive phases (DetectChains state)
%%     Pattern: Same check fails in sequential phase numbers (e.g., P8, P9, P10)
%%     Regex: Extract trailing digits (\d+$) from phase names
%%     Requires: minimum 2 consecutive numbers to qualify as cascading
%%
%% D5: Threshold rule for recurring advice (ApplyThreshold state)
%%     Criterion: count >= 5 for same failure name
%%     Rationale: Identifies systematic failures worthy of design review
%%     Message: "テンプレート改善を推奨: {check} ({count}回失敗)"
%%
%% D6: Optional output sections (WriteOutliers, WriteClassification)
%%     Implementation: Conditional output via spread operator
%%     Benefit: Avoids cluttering TOON with empty arrays/objects
%%     Spec: D-RQ-6 (omit empty sections)
%%
%% D7: Parallel write execution (WriteTopFailure, WriteOutliers, WriteClassification)
%%     Note: Shown as parallel for conceptual clarity; actual implementation
%%     is single pass through analytics-toon.ts writeAnalyticsToon() function
%%     Justification: Independent section construction with shared output buffer
